In this video we will see with more details
what a comet is.

2
00:00:10,030 --> 00:00:13,930
They are very small bodies
with a diameter not much larger than a few

3
00:00:13,930 --> 00:00:16,780
kilometres
and composed of 80% of water ice

4
00:00:16,780 --> 00:00:22,360
as well as organic compounds
such as carbon, hydrogen, oxygen and nitrogen.

5
00:00:22,360 --> 00:00:27,759
Comets come from a large spherical cloud
at the limit of the solar system, known as

6
00:00:27,759 --> 00:00:30,789
the Oort Cloud,
named after the Dutch astronomer

7
00:00:30,789 --> 00:00:35,510
who first suggested its existence.
The spherical geometry of the cloud and its

8
00:00:35,510 --> 00:00:39,720
supposed size
of the order of 100'000 astronomical units,

9
00:00:39,720 --> 00:00:42,790
that is, 100'000 times the size of the Earth
orbit,

10
00:00:42,790 --> 00:00:45,410
are deduced from the fact that the orbits
of comets have

11
00:00:45,410 --> 00:00:49,780
sometimes an extreme eccentricity, so they
are extremely elongated.

12
00:00:49,780 --> 00:00:53,730
They have sometimes very long orbital periods
up to several centuries,

13
00:00:53,730 --> 00:00:57,470
such as the Halley comet with a period of
76 years,

14
00:00:57,470 --> 00:01:00,870
and the orbital inclinations are distributed
almost randomly.

15
00:01:00,870 --> 00:01:04,040
In other words, comets come
randomly from all directions.

16
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:08,760
At the distance of the Oort cloud,
the gravitational forces from stars other

17
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:11,720
than the Sun
are not negligible any more, so that from

18
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:14,740
time to time,
a small gravitational perturbation

19
00:01:14,740 --> 00:01:19,500
caused by stars in the Milky Way are able
to pull a comet out of the cloud and through

20
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:25,330
it toward the Sun.
In some way, the Oort cloud is

21
00:01:25,330 --> 00:01:29,950
a natural reservoir of comets
created at the same time as the solar system.

22
00:01:29,950 --> 00:01:35,370
This is why the study of comets is so essential.
They consist in genuine fossils of our solar

23
00:01:35,370 --> 00:01:39,080
system
composed of the primordial matter that formed

24
00:01:39,080 --> 00:01:43,850
the planets
and that may be at the origin of life.

25
00:01:43,850 --> 00:01:48,840
Here are two cometary nuclei visited by the
