26
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:56,690
Left is Tempel 1 with a diameter of 7.6 km
and right is Hartley 2 with a very small nucleus

27
00:01:56,690 --> 00:02:00,710
of 2.2 km wide.
When a comet approaches the Sun, the surface

28
00:02:00,710 --> 00:02:04,420
of the nucleus melts
and matter is ejected to form large and diffuse

29
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:07,820
tails
such as here with the comet Hale-Bopp.

30
00:02:07,820 --> 00:02:13,150
You see here the blue ionised tail, composed
